<p>The <em>Finder</em> is MacOS’ equivalent to <em>Windows Explorer</em> and is handy to use due to useful systemwide shortcuts.</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="new-finder-tab---t">New Finder-Tab (⌘ + T)</h2>

<p>Generating a new tab in the finder window is as simple as just using the <strong>Command + T</strong> Shortcut.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/2021-02-07-new-tab.gif" alt="Image for generating a new Tab" />
<em>New finder tab in action.</em></p>

<hr />

<h2 id="copy---c--paste---v">Copy (⌘ + C) + Paste (⌘ + V)</h2>

<p>Copying and pasting files works with the shortcuts <code>Command + C / Command + V</code>.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/2021-02-14-copy-paste.gif" alt="Image for generating a new Tab" />
<em>Copy/Paste in action.</em></p>

<hr />

<h2 id="new-folder-----n">New Folder (⌘ + ⇧ + N)</h2>

<p>Creating a new folder is done by Command + Shift + N.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/2021-02-07-new-tab.gif" alt="Image for generating a new Tab" />
<em>New folder tab in action.</em></p>

<hr />

